.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd April 25, 2026
.Dt try-hard 1
.Os try-hard
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm try-hard
.Nd retries a command multiple times in case of failure
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm try-hard
max_trials
max_delay
.br
.Op Fl m Ar min_delay | Fl Fl min-delay Ar min_delay
.br
.Op Fl A Ar delay_increment | Fl Fl additive-increase Ar delay_increment
.br
.Op Fl M Ar delay_factor | multiplicative-increase Ar delay_factor
.br
.Op Fl T Ar max_delay | Fl Fl truncate-delay Ar truncated_max_delay
.br
.Op Fl D | Fl Fl deterministic
.br
.Op Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
.Op Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
.br
--
command ...
.Nm try-hard
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm try-hard
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm try-hard
tries to run a command up to a given number of trials. In case of failure, a certain delay time span is waited before the next trial.
.br
The delay to wait is by default randomly chosen (using random-sleep) from the interval [min_delay, max_delay]. Alternatively, in deterministic mode, the delay is always max_delay.
.br
For each new trial, it is possible to increase max_delay by a multiplicative-increase factor as well as an additive-increase increment. The new max_delay can be truncated by truncated_max_delay, to prevent further increases.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl m Ar min_delay | Fl Fl min-delay Ar min_delay
Sets the minimum delay min_delay (default: 0.0).
.It Fl A Ar delay_increment | Fl Fl additive-increase Ar delay_increment
Sets the additive-increase delay increment (default: 0.0).
.It Fl M Ar delay_factor | multiplicative-increase Ar delay_factor
Sets the multiplicative-increase delay factor (default: 1.0).
.It Fl T Ar max_delay | Fl Fl truncate-delay Ar truncated_max_delay
Sets the truncated_max_delay for limiting the increase of max_delay (default: 31536000.0, i.e. 1 year).
.It Fl D | Fl Fl deterministic
Sets deterministic mode, i.e. turns off randomisation of the delay.
.It Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: no output is made.
.It Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
Verbose mode: print selected delay and wake-up.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints the program's command-line parameters and exits.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints the program version and exits.
.El
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It try-hard 10 60 --verbose -- git clone https://dreibh@github.com/dreibh/rserpooldemo.git
.It try-hard 3 300 -q -- git clone https://git.freebsd.org/ports.git
.It try-hard 3 65.5 -- wget -O example.tar.gz https://www.example.net/example.tar.gz
.It try-hard 10 1.0 -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 2.0 --min-delay 1.0 --multiplicative-increase 2.0 --truncate-delay 3600.0 -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 1.0 -m 1 -M 2 -T 3600 -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 1 --min-delay 0.5 --additive-increase 5 --truncate-delay 300 -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 1 -m 1 -A 5 -T 300 -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 1.0 --deterministic -w -- false
.It try-hard 10 1.0 -D -w -- false
.It try-hard --version
.It try-hard --help
.El
